2.  **Create an `apple-app-site-association` file:**
    *   This file MUST be served from the root of your domain (`https://myapp.com/apple-app-site-association`)
        or from the `.well-known` subdirectory (`https://myapp.com/.well-known/apple-app-site-association`).
    *   It MUST be served with `Content-Type: application/json`.
    *   It MUST be accessible via HTTPS.
    *   Example content for `apple-app-site-association` file:

        {
          "applinks": {
            "apps": [],
            "details": [
              {
                "appID": "YOUR_TEAM_ID.com.yourcompany.UniversalLinksPromoApp", // Replace with your actual Team ID and Bundle Identifier
                "paths": [ "/promo/*", "*" ]
              }
            ]
          }
        }
        
        *   **`YOUR_TEAM_ID`**: You can find this in Xcode > Project Navigator > Project > Signing & Capabilities, it's the 10-character alphanumeric string.
        *   **`com.yourcompany.UniversalLinksPromoApp`**: Replace with your app's actual Bundle Identifier.
        *   **`"paths": [ "/promo/*", "*" ]`**: This tells iOS which paths on your domain are handled by your app. `/promo/*` means any path starting with `/promo/`. `*` means all paths. Be specific as needed.

